En la Biblia Hebrea a veces se refiere a una sola deidad; particularmente al Elohe de Israel; otras veces se refiere a deidades en plural.

Nota: No usamos “elohim” para referirse a Yahweh Elohe de Yisrael.
English:
Mighty ones

In the Hebrew Bible, elohim (Hebrew: אֱלֹהִים [(ʔ)eloˈ(h)im]) sometimes refers to a single deity, particularly (but not always) the Elohe of Israel,[1][2] at other times it refers to deities in the plural.

Note: We do not use “elohim” to refer to our Yahweh Elohe of Yisrael.
